  # Get Analysis Job

  Retrieves the status and results of an analysis job.

  ## Path Parameters
  - `jobId` (required): The job ID returned from creating an analysis job

  ## Response
  Returns job details including:
  - `id`: Job ID
  - `url`: Original URL analyzed
  - `status`: Current status (PENDING, SCRAPING, ANALYZING, COMPLETED, FAILED)
  - `analysis`: Analysis results (null if not completed)
  - `metadata`: Processing metadata
    - `tokensUsed`: Number of tokens used
    - `processingMs`: Processing time in milliseconds
    - `createdAt`: Job creation timestamp
    - `completedAt`: Job completion timestamp (null if not completed)

  ## Status Values
  - `PENDING`: Job is queued, waiting to be processed
  - `SCRAPING`: Currently scraping the website
  - `ANALYZING`: Currently analyzing with Gemini
  - `COMPLETED`: Analysis completed successfully
  - `FAILED`: Analysis failed (check error message)
}
